text: Reynolds Field is a 1,500-seat multi-purpose stadium in Roseville, Minnesota, United States. It is home to the University of Northwestern – St. Paul Eagles. The facility was dedicated in honor of long-time coach Chub Reynolds in September 1990. The stadium was rebuilt in 2014.
